The paper discusses the application of data science and engineering techniques for mapping input factors to crop throughput, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). It also discusses the collection and processing of distributed data, which falls under the categories of data management (cs.DB) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also touches upon the economic costs and benefits of digital agriculture, which could fall under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR) or computational economics (cs.CE).
